:: Add even more dark pattern ideas (different sized buttons). {"position":"500,1075","size":"100,100"}
In an attempt to impress the client further, you decide to add additional dark patterns. You make some buttons larger and more prominent than others, nudging users towards specific actions. You believe these enhancements will increase the website's effectiveness.

Some weeks pass...

Unexpectedly, while scrolling through reddit, you see your clients company name in a developer reddit thread for being unethical! 

<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rsolis096/CMPT-376w/main/resources/images/reddit.png" alt="Reddit Image" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">

You think... stuff like this happens all the time but it's just one post, right? The website starts picking up more negative attention in the online community. This time, the criticism is even harsher. The site is labeled as a prime example of unethical design, and some users threaten to boycott the company.

You think about what this entails for a moment. 

Nobody will know it was you who developing so it won't necessarily affect your career. Not only that but you still have more Dark UX Patterns that the client wants to A/B test.

How do you respond?

(set: $storyPath to $storyPath + (a:"Added even more dark pattern features"))

[[Everyone’s got something to say, whatever. Continue work as normal]]

[[Maybe they have a point....]]


:: Comply with the supervisor's and client's requests, even though you realize the design might be unethical {"position":"2650,1000","size":"100,100"}
Despite your concerns about the potential confusion and ethical implications of the clients request, you proceed to implement the changes exactly as requested.

Some time after your implementation is deployed, your team is invited to a celebration.

Turns out the client is pleased by your work and has recorded a significant increase in revenue since the new design went live. However, you can't shake off the feeling that something is wrong.

At the celebration, you overhear some of the client’s managers discussing your implementation and you find out that there was a small increase in refunds from users who unintentionally purchased the protection plan as well as complaints regarding accessibility for visual impaired users, causing these users to have important information about their purchase obscured.

(set: $storyPath to $storyPath + (a:"Complied with Supervisor and implemented the design"))

