:: ENDING C {"position":"1350,1750","size":"100,100"}
The client notices that they have sub-par profits. They complete an investigation and notice that the company didn't implement the red left button and green right button for agreeing to the protected warranty. There were also additional features added like a pop-up confirmation that the client didn't agree to. 

The client tells the company this button option was an explicit ask to boost profits for their protected warranty. They warn the company that they will find another business partner if proper action is not taken to ensure this doesn't happen in the future.

The head of the department and your supervisor call you for a meeting. They criticize you for implementing these changes without notifying anyone and for disobeying the client's demands.

You are moved to another project and your changes are reverted by someone else from your department.

[[Finish]]


